Hi Team,

Does jenkinsapi support parameterized build in Jenkinsfile (pipeline as code)?

Here is my pipeline as code (Jenkinsfile):
================================================
''''''''''
pipeline {
    agent { label 'NODE1' }
  stages {
    stage ('Provider') {
      steps {
  script {
   def name
   def userInput = input(
    id: 'userInput', message: 'testing params',
                parameters: [
     string(defaultValue: 'Rajesh',
                           description: 'Enter The Name you want.',
                           name: 'name')
    ]
   )
   env.name = userInput.name?:'Rajesh'
  }
  sh "echo ${name}"
   }
    }
  }
}
''''''''''
I am trying to build this job by supplying parameters as:
''''''''''''''''
>>> from jenkinsapi.jenkins import Jenkins
>>> J = Jenkins(JENKINS_URL,username,XXXXXXXXXX',ssl_verify=False)
>>> J.build_job('PythonTrigger',{'name':'Rajesh'})
''''''''''''''''
And the error, I am getting is:
''''''''''''''''''''''
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "<stdin>", line 1, in <module>
  File "/usr/local/lib/python3.6/site-packages/jenkinsapi/jenkins.py", line 203, in build_job
    self[jobname].invoke(build_params=params or {})
  File "/usr/local/lib/python3.6/site-packages/jenkinsapi/job.py", line 179, in invoke
    raise BadParams("This job does not support parameters")
jenkinsapi.custom_exceptions.BadParams: This job does not support parameters

'''''''''''''''''''''''
Please help in this issue.

now they are done by description:
def __setitem__(self, description, credential)
def __delitem__(self, description)

but description is not unique, however credential_id is.

Am I right？If I am right, I can write the code,but we need to talk about how do we deal with the previous code.
